  "prompt": "What does President Duterte think of Donald Trump?",
  "response": "President Rodrigo Duterte of the Philippines has expressed positive views about former U.S. President Donald Trump. During Trump's presidency, Duterte praised Trump's leadership and even called him a \"good friend.\" They had a seemingly cordial relationship, with Trump inviting Duterte to the White House, though the visit never materialized due to scheduling conflicts.\n\nDuterte appreciated Trump's straightforward and pragmatic approach to foreign policy, particularly Trump's decision to reduce U.S. involvement in international conflicts, which aligned with Duterte's own stance on sovereignty and non-interference. Additionally, Duterte was supportive of Trump's \"America First\" policy, seeing it as a way for the Philippines to pursue its own independent foreign policy.\n\nHowever, it's worth noting that Duterte's opinions on international figures can sometimes shift, and his views should be understood within the context of Philippine-U.S. relations and his administration's broader foreign policy goals.",
